HEADWORD: Mico
<hw>Mi"co</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp. or Pg.
<ets>mico</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small South American
monkey (<spn>Mico melanurus</spn>), allied to the marmoset. The name was
originally applied to an albino variety.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

